71.4% of the respondents experienced stress from school, making it the most common
stressor during the COVID-19 lockdown (Table 5). 38.6% (85) of the respondents felt this stress
affected them negatively in terms of mental health and well-being. The 5-point Likert scale
analysis (Table 6) reveals an evident increase in academic stress from school due to the
lockdown. Excessive homework from school was found to be the most recurrent stressor,
